_:Nd2ddc44288bb4e5880860960efa32944 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Helen Wylie is Director General for the Digital and Transformation Group at the Department for Work and Pensions (<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>). She was appointed to this role in May 2025.</p>\n\n<p>Helen is also Chief Digital and Information Officer (<abbr title=\"Chief Digital and Information Officer\">CDIO</abbr>) at <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>, a role she took up in November 2024 and retains as part of her current remit.</p>\n\n<p>Helen joined <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> in 2018. Prior to becoming <abbr title=\"Chief Digital and Information Officer\">CDIO</abbr>, Helen held various Digital Director roles across <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>, most latterly as Chief Technology Officer, and played a key role in <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>’s wider service modernisation agenda, helping to shape the organisation for the future.</p>\n\n<p>Before this, Helen worked in a range of senior technology and digital delivery roles across both the public and private sectors, including at the Bank of England, Experian, and TNT Post Group. Helen is strongly people focused and passionate about improving the vital public services <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> provides.</p>\n\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
